#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid "South Gate Station Security Uniform"
msgid_plural "South Gate Station Security Uniform"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str_sp': 'South Gate Station Security Uniform'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid ""
"The standard and uniformly dull blue uniform worn by most members of the "
"South Gate Station security detail. Often associated with bravery, or a "
"quick death."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid "Cave Hopper Leather Armor"
msgid_plural "Cave Hopper Leather Armor"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str_sp': 'Cave Hopper Leather Armor'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid ""
"A rather lightweight armor protecting user's vital torso area, in addition "
"to some arm protection. This armor is made of cave hopper leather. ."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid "South Gate Station security vest"
msgid_plural "South Gate Station security vest"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str_sp': 'South Gate Station security vest'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid ""
"A nylon vest equipped with several pouches for magazine and ammunition "
"storage. Comes pre-equipped with several light ballistic plates that provide"
" a small modicum of protection."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid "Underrail Metal Armor"
msgid_plural "Underrail Metal Armors"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Underrail Metal Armor'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid ""
"Near all-encompasing suit of metal armor. Outfitted with enough steel plates"
" to cover the overwhelming majority of the user's body. Its immense "
"protection comes with a drawback: its immense weight and incumberence for "
"all but strong users."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid "Underrail metal helmet"
msgid_plural "Underrail metal helmets"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Underrail metal helmet'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid ""
"A helmet made from plates of steel with a visor of ballistic glass. Made for"
" use in tandem with underrail metal armor."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_crossbows.json
msgid "Zephyr crossbow"
msgid_plural "Zephyr crossbows"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_crossbows.json
msgid ""
"A light crossbow common amongst the more poor denizens of the underrail.  "
"Stronger people can reload it much faster.  Bolts fired from this weapon "
"have a good chance of remaining intact for re-use. Why one would use these "
"instead of firearms is unknown, but many swear by them."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_crossbows.json
msgid "Cyclon crossbow"
msgid_plural "Cyclon crossbows"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_crossbows.json
msgid ""
"A high-power crossbow with with an intricate 4-bar mechanism to reduce felt "
"load when tensing the crossbow.  Takes less time to reload due to a modern "
"string-pulling system, but comes at the expense of stopping power."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_melee.json
msgid "shock steel sledge hammer"
msgid_plural "shock steel sledge hammers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'shock steel sledge hammer'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_melee.json
msgid ""
"A large, heavy hammer.  Makes an acceptable melee weapon for the very "
"strong, but is nearly useless in the hands of the weak. This variant has "
"been outfitted with electrodes, making it useful to shock people with."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_melee.json
msgid "shock dagger"
msgid_plural "shock daggerss"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'shock dagger', 'str_pl': 'shock daggerss'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_melee.json
msgid ""
"This is a combat knife common to the underrail.  It is light and extremely "
"sharp, and could be deadly in either the right hands or when attached as a "
"bayonet. This version has been outfitted with electrodes, allowing the user "
"to shock their target before going in for a stab."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid "Hawker extended magazine"
msgid_plural "Hawker extended magazines"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Hawker extended magazine'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid ""
"An extended 28-round polymer magazine for use with standard round compatible"
" firearms."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid "Hawker magazine"
msgid_plural "Hawker magazines"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Hawker magazine'}
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid ""
"A compact light-weight polymer magazine for use with 5mm standard round "
"compatible firearms."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid "Hawker pistol"
msgid_plural "Hawker pistols"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid ""
"A weak pistol common amongst all strata of the underrail, from the lowest "
"junkyard mutant to the highest protectorate officer. Prized by all for its "
"ease of use, low production costs, and relatively common ammunition."
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid "South Gate laser pistol"
msgid_plural "South Gate laser pistols"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid ""
"This model of laser pistol is one of a rare type in the underail. Most "
"denizens of the underrail are more than content to meet their death at the "
"hands of a firearm, but few are ready for a laser weapon!"
msgstr ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid "Acid Pistol"
msgid_plural "Acid Pistols"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_pistols.json
msgid ""
"A curious and rare pistol in the underrail. What's not so curious is what "
"its acid vials do to your skin when they want to dissolve it into its base "
"components."
msgstr ""

